description: The Grays are a cursed family. Dorian Gray IV, the last of his line, struggles with the realization that his personal demons are exactly that…a supernatural force that plagues not only the Grays but many of society’s wealthiest families. Convinced his redemption is only secured through ridding the city of demons called the Morbi, Dorian launches an ongoing crusade for his soul.
name: Beginnings

description:
The Man, The Myth, The Amulet? Legendary star of the small and silver screen, ADAM WEST, has his career youth-enized in this hip-whimsical,trans-dimensional epic of an adventure. When a mysterious fan delivers an exotic amulet to Mr. West’s doorstep he is Dorothy-fied on an odyssey that will change his career, his love life and inadvertently make him the man that saves the universe!

Collects the first The Mis-Adventures of Adam West mini-series.
name: Volume 1

description: Hyacinthe, Dungeon Keeper to be, continues to render justice in a cloak nightly as The Night Shirt and stumbles upon the one he pines for, Alexandra, an assassin, about to be raped! After his valiant and heroic rescue, his wettest dreams come true with dire consequences. Years later, he's married and a poor husband, worse even, a poor lover, until Alexandra plots to gain him back.
name: Innocence Lost

description: The critically acclaimed miniseries mixing horror & heart from AICN Comics writer Mark L. Miller gets collected! Nanny & Hank are ready for their golden years, but a blood-drunk vampire turns their life upside down! Now the elderly pair must deal with becoming creatures of the night & take care of their ornery grandkids too!
name: Retirement Is Hell

description: The sold out comic series comes to you in trade paperback form. The next generation of characters that have made Bluewater famous comes the most infamous of them all Take youthful energy. Add in some over-active imagination. Mix in some powdered donuts. Sprinkle it with delusional disorder and you get ... Insane Jane! The kookiest action hero of the 21st century. Will Jane save the day? Will Jane destroy the world? Will she remember to take her medication?
name: TPB

description: Comic's most crazed champion is back! Trapped in a "Hospital for the Mentally Unhinged," our loony lion-heart must fight for her freedom and survival. With the help of her trusty new side-kick, the forces of evil are on the run. Or, maybe she's just imagining this. Either way, Jane's back and she's crazier than ever!
name: TPB

description: Dan Abnett and Andy Lanning finish the first arc of their cosmic superhero masterpiece in the making and will have you begging for more! It's the return of Prismatica as she rejoins the Hypernaturals and faces her greatest fear: the man who killed her husband and the most diabolical supervillain the Quantinuum has ever known . . . Sublime.
name: The Bad Trip.

description: FINAL ISSUE! All great journeys must come to an end...The assault on Wraithendal continues as Valen Brand's quest to reclaim his stolen soul from the necromancer Korrus Null reaches its shocking conclusion. Don't miss the final chapter of the epic fantasy series from fan-favorite writer Michael Alan Nelson (28 DAYS LATER, ROBERT E. HOWARD'S HAWKS OF OUTREMER) and rising star DEADPOOL artist Matteo Scalera!

Violet Rose is a self-proclaimed sixth grader super-sleuth, a foster child who discovers that many of the people in her normal suburban town are actually supernatural beings hiding in seemingly ordinary lives. With best friends Lindsey and Ciara, a spirit from a Renoir painting, Violet is a little detective that never gives up, solving cases after her homework is done while learning about the magical gift her grandfather gave her before he passed.
name: TPB

description: Adjusting to modern day life is one thing. Fighting the female assassin Silencer is another. Worse, one of Judo Girl's (Diana Moore) most dangerous adversaries from the 1960s resurfaces to complicate her life, Lincoln Stanley, aka Hep Cat. Has he really reformed, as he claims, or is he back to his old tricks? Check out this exclusive, never-before-seen, Judo Girl story!

After 40 years in suspended animation, Judo Girl is on a quest to find her missing brother. And her old enemy, Captain Steel, hasn't exactly spent the last four decades collecting rust either! On the flip-side is a retro story set during the era of go-go boots and slot cars revealing the secret origin of the original Steel Ray!

Trade paperback collecting issues from the first Judo Girl mini-series.
name: The Beginning

description: Adjusting to modern day life is one thing. Fighting the female assassin Silencer is another. Worse, one of Judo Girl's (Diana Moore) most dangerous adversaries from the 1960s resurfaces to complicate her life, Lincoln Stanley, aka Hep Cat. Has he really reformed, as he claims, or is he back to his old tricks? This gallery collection features exclusive Judo Girl art!

This special, free one shot includes bonus material never before seen. Greek mythology has documented the nine Muses, the inspirational daughters of the almighty Zeus. But history forgot one-- the Tenth Muse. Emma, Brett, and Dawn were the best of friends-- until Emma disappeared, leaving only a note saying goodbye. Now, eight years later, Emma is back, without answers. What happened to Emma? What is her connection with Grayson Bishop, and, most of all, how did ordinary Emma Sonnet become the mysterious TENTH MUSE? Introducing The Tenth Muse, a new kind of super-hero saga unlike anything you've ever seen before. A mystery. An action series. A character-driven saga that will bring you to the edge of your seat. See if you can unravel the mystery of The 10th Muse.. Apologies for the blurred cover image, but there is a new celebrity modeling as the Tenth Muse, and it has to be kept a secret until she makes it public!

10 years ago this book from IMAGE COMICS blasted onto the scene as the 6th highest selling comic book. Covers by famed comic book artists like Chris Bachelo (X-Men), Andy Park (Tomb Raider), Randy Green (Witchblade), Roger Cruz (Spiderman) were published. Now in one place you will find the best of the best of 10 years of covers. Greek mythology has documented the nine Muses, the inspirational daughters of the almighty Zeus. But history forgot one--the 10th Muse. Come celebrate 10 years with a cover by Ken Lashley and JD Smith.

name: Sterven als een Hond in de Sneeuw

description: Actually issue 1953 #15-16

Did you ever wonder how to stop brooding if your ears are protruding? Or how to indulge yourself and snore without being a bore? Or for the masochists among you, how to sit on a tack? Or for the narcissists, how to contemplate the back of your pate? Or something as simple as how to get out of bed gracefully? Or something a bit more challenging like how to boot a fly off your snoot? Or, if you’re the violent type, what’s the best way to kick someone in the teeth? Or, for those striving for greater refinement, how to be particular and is perpendicular? If these conundrums have perplexed and mystified you, the remedy is at hand: cartooning genius Basil Wolverton’s “Culture Corner,” an indispensable guide to demystifying life’s most worrisome and disconcerting social quandaries.
name: HC

description: In this first episode we are introduced to Shaky our narrator. Shaky is short for 'Shakespeare' the nickname he has earned because he was a writer before the Crossed. It is through the entries in Shaky's diary that we the readers will get to observe the fate of the survivor colony settled in on Cava a small islet in the Orkneys North of Scotland.
name: Episode 1

description: In this episode we are treated to Shaky's narration of his experience when the Crossed first occurred and more of his chilling contemplations.
name: Episode 2

description: In this episode we are introduced to the leaders of Cava. And we begin to see that there may be more to the Crossed than just mindless mayhem.
name: Episode 3

description: A few of the survivors leave Cava to go rabbit hunting where they encounter an elderly woman who is Crossed. This brings back some evil ghosts for one of the survivors.
name: Episode 4

description: After finding some Crossed behavior which seems uncharacteristic, the group calls a meet to discuss the mystery. This leads Shaky to flashback to the early days of the Crossed outbreak and declare that some mysteries are better left unsorted.
name: Episode 5

description: This episode continues Shaky's London flashback and we discover that he had trundled out onto the Millenium Bridge and lept to his death in the face of the madness...
name: Episode 6

description: Sex, as one might imagine, is a constant thought on the minds of the survivors. But this time, as a distraction, it leads to an unimaginable horror.
name: Episode 7

description: The proposed "sortie" to go find supplies and other survivors shifts from being voluntary to being decided by a lottery and a father has to do the unspeakable.
name: Episode 8

description: A duo of Crossed trapped on an escarpment leads Shaky to flashback to London when he was pulled from the Thames by river police and the inevitable result of a governmental rescue mission.
name: Episode 9

description: Shaky's London flashback continues and he discovers that the survivors stuck on Cava may not be all that different from the Crossed.
name: Episode 10

description: Shaky muses on how terror is at least a relief from the boredom. Also a young soldier demonstrates his honor as he sets off to correct a smug teens mistake, a mistake which may cost the survivors dearly.
name: Episode 11

description: The survivors learn the hard way why the upcoming "sortie" requires a lottery. If they send volunteers then only the useless and cowardly would remain.
name: Episode 12

description: The loner Jackson arrives and Shaky considers what it takes to survive all alone. This leads him to flashback to his own early days of survival and some of his mistakes.
name: Episode 13

description: Jackson has news of the Crossed bizarre behavior. It seems as if they are planning, learning. Jackson's arrival has also forced Shaky to reconsider the upcoming "sortie" as well as the nature of madness, cowardice and survival. See he has encountered others like Jackson, cruel, survival-of-the-fittest types who prey upon the weak. But they survive.
name: Episode 14

description: This episode the topic is love and relationships. Shaky considers all the various romantic possibilities then finally settles into a conversation with and about Tabitha. See Tabitha is a bit of a hippy and her free spirit in the face of all the surrounding horror is very attractive. Beyond that she sees Shaky as a fellow artist and reminds him that art has it's own reward beyond self-centered attention getting. This was also a hard lesson Shaky learned during his time with the "Gamekeeper" and his crew just outside of London.
name: Episode 15

description: Shaky gets Tabitha to create a distraction which only ends up helping him to refine his plan. He also recalls his early days in Mr. Tooley's crew just outside of London. Tooley is called "The Gamekeeper" because he used to work the estate of Thackery's and now he is the de facto leader of a small band which includes his former employers. It is an ironic turn of events which further illuminates Shaky's thoughts on cowardice, madness and leadership.
name: Episode 16

description:
On a routine trip to check on their boat, a small group of survivors discovers that the Crossed may not be as predictable as they had been counting on.

Shaky recalls a similar event from his time in the Gamekeepers crew. When the Crossed predictability was like clockwork.
name: Episode 17

description: This episode we get a little closer glimpse at Sophia and her tragic story. On Cava there is a currency among the men. The availability of Sophia's body. Shaky has been saving up and chooses this moment to cash in.
name: Episode 18

description: Sofia, deaf and mute, used by most of the men on Cava as currency has finally reached her tragic end. Shaky is amazed by what people will endure in order to survive. And his plan is now in ruins.
name: Episode 19

description: In this episode Shaky delves into true darkness as he forces his plan to go into effect. His motto is "You do whatever you must to get whatever you need". This is his refined version of what he learned during his days with the "Gamekeeper".
name: Episode 20

person_credits.name: Jack T. Chick
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Shaky muses over a photo of himself.
name: Interlude 1

volume.name: Crossed: Wish You Were Here Interlude

description: Shaky considers the Island of Cava itself and fellow survivor Elisa.
name: Interlude 2

volume.name: Crossed: Wish You Were Here Interlude

description: Shaky muses on humor at the end of the world and four more of his fellow survivors.
name: Interlude 3

volume.name: Crossed: Wish You Were Here Interlude

description: Shaky considers the cause of the Crossed outbreak and the idiocy of even bothering. He also muses on four fellow survivors.
name: Interlude 4

volume.name: Crossed: Wish You Were Here Interlude

description: Shaky amuses himself by creating a creation myth for Cava as well as musing upon five of his fellow survivors.
name: Interlude 5

volume.name: Crossed: Wish You Were Here Interlude

description: Shaky considers his impulse to check the internet at the end of the world. He also muses upon a few more of his fellow survivors.
name: Interlude 6

volume.name: Crossed: Wish You Were Here Interlude
